<font color="#FF0000">THANKS TO ALL, REALLY...</font><br>
<tt>Mon Apr 28 20:48:09 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Brief facts regarding my visit:<br><br>
1. The Air Show at El Toro Marine Base was the annual thing, but this year was the last one as base will close, so instead of 500,000 on each day, they got almost 1 million each day, Stealth Fly over on Sat, Blue Angels both days. Kind of regular day in the sun for the locals here.  The Marine Air Show will continue next year at Mira Mar (San Deigo).<br><br>
2. I had read the Traveling War Wall was coming into town again and would be in Little Saigon. Not connected to the Air Show.  I don't know, frankly, if there was any Vietnamese occasion going on....as wierd as this sounds, It just wasn't &quot;ok&quot; with me to strike up conversations, with strangers, Vietnamese or _____ (what's the right word for here: American doesn't seem right, Whites?, Non Asians? Help me out gang). I didn't plan to go, I just decided to and 30 minutes later I was on the Freeway, looking for that sign that says &quot;Little Saigon&quot;. I think alot of what happened after than was on autopilot, and I am digesting it slowly.<br>
Per the article ( http://www.ocregister.com/news/1997/0497/042897/fall.html ) it was in conjunction with the Fall of Saigon and hosted by the Vietnamese community. <br><br>
3. Other than reading the article in the local paper the next day, (The Register - Orange County), I don't think nor noticed any &quot;special&quot; holiday or other event other than the Wall being there. Maybe there was and I was either culturally blind, or in more &quot;shock&quot; than I realized.  The clash over the flags with the City Council indicates that this was hosted by a Vietnamese Organization, as I understand it.<br><br>
4. John, your pointer about the younger generation assimilating was excellant. They are, including a big rise in street crime, Cafe society, and driveby and home invasion robberies and shootings. Just like the locals do. And (to keep the balance) Univ of Calif at Irvine is over 50% Asian, and the G.P.A.'s there would scare Albert Einstein.<br>
5.Doc, your reference to Cuba is also right on the mark. And I also thank you for the prior post, the apology was not needed but is welcomed. My mental stumbling has caused others pain and discomfort, and yes, I wish I could backtrack both in time and cyberspace, at least back enough to erase those damn &quot;firebrand&quot; comments...but back then, (was it only 6 months?) I used to think that PTSD was mostly a con, vietnam vets were homeless rip off artists at the freeway on-ramps with &quot;feed me-god bless-homeless vet&quot; cardboard signs and haircuts/clothing right out of the schizo ward, and they all lived drunkenly under then nearest bridge (homeless do that in Southern Calif).  I am rather proud of my &quot;education&quot; from then, hell I brag about to friends of my who are not fed up with my bragging about this site anyway.  And why not brag, Damn, I have some fine teachers on this site.  <br><br>
doc spatz<br><br>

